We began working on a mobile app called Balance Wallet

It was a beautifully designed application but was terribly engineered

We had made a terrible choiceâ€”using React Native over Swiftâ€”which slowed us down enormously and cost me financially

I was proud of the concepts we tried https://t.co/HJghda8wLH

One of our engineers, @pedrouid, came up with the idea for @WalletConnect which we decided to spin out into its own entity

This was an enormously complicated and time consuming endeavour for a microscopic startup but it was well worth it

Pedro has done a fantastic job with it https://t.co/xV72lxhkQQ

We pioneered an incredible amount of the standard interface patterns for Ethereum

Balance Manager, a web app for interacting with the protocol, helped thousands of people move hundreds of millions of dollars of value around the network

Products for Protocols for People âš–ï¸ https://t.co/uvmrEI9tYm

I had helped out on a few of the early concepts for Ethereum and was paid in Ether

Watching this open source cryptocurrency skyrocket while my closed source indie app imploded was wild

It sucked me back into the ecosystem and we pivoted Balance to focus on Ethereum-based apps https://t.co/dWRDUJfkSi

After our successful launch on the Mac App Store, things went swiftly downhill for our beautiful little product

Intuit, a gigantic corporation that controls a lot of banking data and accounting software, pulled their data from Plaid, which ruined us

Then ETH went up 100x https://t.co/BmDh5EufYa
